--ANSWER TO TRIVIA QUESTION: 

  Q.  What is the longest word in the Bible?
 
  A.  Mahershalalhashbaz
      It's the name of Isaiah's son

      See Isaiah 8:1

      "The LORD said to me, 'Take a large scroll and 
      write on it with an ordinary pen:
      Maher-Shalal-Hash-Baz.'" 

      This name means quick to the plunder, swift 
      to the spoil.    


